# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tauri POS — environment template (committed; copy to .env.local for dev).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vite env load order (high → low priority), so the LAST file wins:
#   .env.development.local   ← mode-specific, user-local (HIGHEST in dev)
#   .env.local               ← user-local, all modes
#   .env.development         ← mode-specific, committed
#   .env                     ← all modes, committed
#
# GOTCHA (the connection bug this documents): in DEV mode a stale
# .env.development.local pointing at PRODUCTION silently overrides .env.local,
# so the dev build hits api.warehouse14.de over mTLS and the dev fingerprint
# is rejected → PIN-login fails / requests 401. If dev can't connect, DELETE
# .env.development.local or make it mirror .env.local (localhost) below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Local dev: talk to the local api-cloud on :3001 (start it via
# apps/mobile/dev/reset-dev-backend.sh; needs OrbStack + postgres).
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001

# Dev device fingerprint — lets PIN-login work WITHOUT a real mTLS client cert.
# PRODUCTION IGNORES THIS (mTLS carries the authoritative device identity there).
# This is the seeded dev device; rotate it for a real dev device.
VITE_DEV_DEVICE_FINGERPRINT=71defad08503fcfb00b0b57e7654b3ed48afb264d34c69c3edb90a65a6b8f698
